Strings are immutable in Java because when a string
is created, it is sent to the String pool. If 
we try to change contents of the string variable
then it throws an error. 

The difference between String and String Builder
is that String is immutable but String Builder's
are mutable. 

The methods of String class are as follows:

1. String.charAt(index);

- String s = "Masai";
- System.out.println(s.charAt(1));
- output is 'a';

2. String.equals(str);

- String s = "Masai";
- String s1 = "Masai";
- s.equals(s1);

3. String.length();

- String s = "Masai";
- s.length();

4. String.indexOf();

- String s = "Masai";
- s.indexOf('a');

5. String.isEmpty();

- String s = "Masai";
- s.isEmpty();